        "questionSubtype": "veryShortAnswer",
        "question": "Name one example of a gaseous solution and state what acts as the solvent in it.",
        "answer": "Example: Air; Solvent: Nitrogen (or Oxygen depending on context, but typically Nitrogen is considered the major component acting as solvent for other gases).",
        "expectedLength": "Name one example and identify the primary solvent gas.",
        "marks": 1,
