        "id": "q3",
        "questionSubtype": "shortAnswer",
        "question": "Define a solution. How does it differ from a general mixture, and what is the key characteristic that makes it 'homogeneous'?",
        "answer": "A solution is a homogeneous mixture of two or more substances where one substance (solute) dissolves in another (solvent). It differs from other mixtures because it is uniform throughout at the molecular level; you cannot see separate parts with the naked eye, and particles do not settle out over time.",
